Preventable Emergency Service Costs

I. Blakley

11/10/2017

Intro

Patients who cannot afford to get outpatient care are forced to rely on emergency services. This shifts the cost of care to the state, the hospital, the insurance company, and the total cost is far higher than the outpatient care would have been, but the individual cannot afford that care and must defer the cost in this way. This results in unnecisarily high costs to the state and decreased overall care for the individual.

The goal of this analysis is to identify diagnosis that should be targets for programs that cover the cost of care for individual who cannot afford it, event after insurance covers some or most of it. These programs could be paid for by the same entities that would have had to pay for the ED visit, and while that may sound unfair, it is ultimatley a savings for them.

limitations -I don’t know the time span of the data we have. This may represent 10 years or 6 months, I don’t know. -I don’t know what the cost to the individual is. If patients are not getting care event thought there is no cost to them, then creating a service to pay for the care will not change anything.

For each case, normalize the count of each diagnosis based on the total number of counts, so you get a proportion. For each diagnosis, is it eaqually likely to be present in somone who is facing multiple crises? Keep in mind, the muli-crisis cases are probably under-represented because the

# divide each count (patient with the diagnosis) by the number of patients in each category (single diagnosis or mulit-diagnosis)
sDiagsFrac = sDiags/sum(count.gen == 1) *100
mDiagsFrac = mDiags/sum(count.gen > 1) *100
m = merge(data.frame(diag=names(sDiagsFrac), 
                                         sDiags=as.numeric(sDiagsFrac)),
                    data.frame(diag=names(mDiagsFrac), 
                                         mDiags=as.numeric(mDiagsFrac)), 
                    all=T)
m[is.na(m)] = 0
plot(m$sDiags, m$mDiags, las=1,
         xlab="patients with this single diagnosis", 
         ylab="patients with this mulitple diagnoses", 
         main="percent of crisis patients with this diagnosis")
abline(a=0, b=1, lty=2)
bigX=5
